The Wishing Tree

I made a wish,
a whispered thought
to the old, gnarled tree
that lifts its limbs
in spring, only to ache
in winter's chill,
with roots that drink
the rain from willing ground.
Hope blooms with every leaf,
as dreams cradle in those branches.

— H.D.

- HD
